    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-05T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="509"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.516/209: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-05T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 5, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120. Referring to Department’s telegram No. 45, June 29, 5 p.m., second
                        paragraph.<note n="20" xml:id="d509fn20">Not printed.</note> Decree law No.
                    98 dated June 25 and published in <hi rend="italic">Official Gazette</hi> dated
                    July 1 reads as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Sole article. Decree law No. 38 of June 16th of the present year is
                            repealed”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Referring to my despatch No. 1184, June 29,<note n="20" xml:id="d509fn21">Not
                        printed.</note> yesterday <persName corresp="#p_GGF1">Garces</persName>,
                    president; <persName corresp="#p_MHE1">Matte</persName>, vice president;
                        <persName corresp="#p_BSA1">Burr</persName>, general manager; and Benavente,
                    secretary, of the Central Bank, resigned stating that they are not in accord
                    with the financial policy of the Junta. These resignations were accepted but
                        <persName corresp="#p_GGF1">Garces</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_MHE1">Matte</persName> continue in their capacity of directors.
                    Principal point in dispute is the industrial development and unemployment relief
                    measure which has been signed but not yet promulgated and which would require
                    the discounting of 190,000,000 pesos of treasury notes with the Central
                    Bank.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
